7950.name: trigonocephaly
7950.description: Premature fusion of the metopic suture causing a triangular forehead.

25530.name: underdeveloped mastoid
25530.description: Hypoplasia of the mastoid process, often congenital or secondary to chronic ear disease.

8328.name: underdevelopment of mastoids
8328.description: Bilateral or unilateral underdevelopment of the mastoid air cells.

8150.name: unilateral exophthalmos
8150.description: Protrusion of one eyeball, often due to mass or inflammation.

8385.name: unilateral nasal cavity mass
8385.description: A mass lesion present on one side of the nasal cavity, may be benign or malignant.

8899.name: unilocular cystic jaw lesion
8899.description: A single-chambered, fluid-filled lesion in the jaw, often odontogenic.

9452.name: upper airway obstruction in a child
9452.description: Partial or complete blockage of the upper respiratory tract in a pediatric patient.

9376.name: vallecular mass
9376.description: Mass lesion located in the vallecula, may cause airway compromise.

8288.name: vascular middle ear mass
8288.description: A vascular-rich tumor or lesion within the middle ear, e.g., glomus tumor.

18629.name: vascular sinonasal mass with flow voids
18629.description: A vascular sinonasal mass showing flow voids on MR, suggestive of a high-flow tumor.

9423.name: vocal cord asymmetry
9423.description: Unequal appearance or position of the vocal cords, may be due to paralysis or mass.

9427.name: vocal cord paralysis or paresis
9427.description: Partial or complete loss of vocal cord mobility, due to neurologic or structural causes.

8998.name: well-defined expansile radiolucent jaw lesion
8998.description: Expansile, well-marginated radiolucent lesion of the jaw bone.

25592.name: wide sutures
25592.description: Abnormal widening of cranial sutures, often seen in increased intracranial pressure or developmental delay.

25593.name: Wormian bones
25593.description: Extra bone pieces within the sutures of the skull, often associated with various syndromes.
